gov.nih.nlm.ling.core

Interface Lexeme

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ContiguousLexeme
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractLexeme, GappedLexeme, MultiWordLexeme, WordLexeme

    public interface Lexeme
    An interface that represents an abstract, non-inflected lexical unit. Such a unit consists of a lemma, a category (which is a generalization of a part-of-speech tag), and the head word. This interface is analogous to a SurfaceElement, but without the textual grounding, i.e., no spans, sentences, etc. If a lexical unit is ambiguous, each sense would be its own lexeme.
    Author:
    Halil Kilicoglu
    See Also:
    AbstractLexeme, ContiguousLexeme, WordLexeme, MultiWordLexeme, GappedLexeme
